Feature: Managing Checklists

This feature is designed to test the main possible, but basic operations a user can perform
in order to manage checklists. Some fundamental connections/ assignments with other CDB objects
might also be tested. Further possible connections/ assignments are tested in the respective feature.

Background:
    Given a project exists


Scenario Outline: Create New Checklist
    When <role> creates a new checklist
    Then a new checklist is <status>

    Examples:
        | role            | status    |
        | Projektmitglied | generated |


Scenario Outline: Create New Checklist From A Template
    Given a checklist template exists
    When <role> creates a new checklist from the template
    Then a new checklist is <status>
        And the attributes from the template are <attr_status>
    Examples:
        | role            | status    | attr_status |
        | Projektmitglied | generated | applied     |


Scenario Outline: Create New Checklist as Quality Gate
    When <role> creates a new quality gate
    Then a new quality gate is <status>

    Examples:
        | role            | status    |
        | Projektmitglied | generated |


Scenario Outline: Create New Checklist as Quality Gate From A Template
    Given a checklist template exists
    When <role> creates a new quality gate from the template
    Then a new quality gate is <status>
        And the attributes from the template are <attr_status>
    Examples:

        | role            | status    | attr_status |
